0.body: Welcome to the Aisopod documentation. Aisopod is an AI-native messaging gateway that bridges the gap between conversational AI and traditional communication channels. Built with Rust, Aisopod provides a robust, type-safe foundation for building AI-driven messaging applications.
0.title: Introduction

1.body: Aisopod enables developers to: Connect AI agents to multiple messaging channels (Slack, Discord, Matrix, etc.) Build intelligent conversational workflows with configurable agents Deploy secure, scalable messaging infrastructure Integrate AI capabilities into existing communication systems
1.title: What is Aisopod?

12.body: After installation, verify that Aisopod is correctly installed: aisopod --version You should see output like: aisopod 0.1.0
12.title: Verify Installation

13.body: Run the onboarding wizard to set up your first configuration: aisopod onboarding The wizard will guide you through: Choose your default LLM provider : Select from supported providers like OpenAI, Anthropic, or Ollama Enter your API key : Securely stored in your OS keychain Configure your default model : Set the model to use for conversations (e.g., gpt-4) Set up a channel (optional) : Connect a messaging platform like Telegram, Discord, or Slack Your configuration is saved to ~/.config/aisopod/config.toml.
13.title: First Run

14.body:
If you prefer to configure manually, create ~/.config/aisopod/config.toml with: [agents.default]
model = "gpt-4" [providers.openai]
api_key = "your-api-key-here" [gateway.bind]
address = "127.0.0.1" [gateway.server]
port = 3000
14.title: Manual Configuration

16.body: Send a message directly from the terminal: aisopod onboarding Then start the gateway in one terminal: aisopod gateway And send a message in another terminal: aisopod message "Hello, what can you do?"

18.body: Aisopod is organized around three core concepts: Gateway : The HTTP/WebSocket server that receives messages and routes them to agents. Agent : An LLM-backed conversational entity with a system prompt, model selection, and bound skills. Channel : An integration with an external messaging platform (Telegram, Discord, Slack, etc.). Channel → Gateway → Agent → LLM Provider ↕ Skills / Tools
18.title: Architecture Overview

19.body: A message arrives via a Channel (e.g., Telegram, Discord) The Gateway receives and authenticates the request The message is routed to the appropriate Agent The Agent processes the message using the configured LLM provider The response flows back through the gateway to the channel
19.title: How It Works
